<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-22T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-22T18:00:00-05:00" n="695" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d695">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/1357</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRP1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-22T18:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 22, 1915, 6 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department would like much to have exact, or at least approximate,
                                number of bales of American cotton seized by Great Britain first and
                                last since the order in council of March 11, and number of these for
                                which to this time full payment has been made.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>